Q:1/4=72
K:Amix
H:Walk through the chanter in 2nds, 3rds, 4ths, and 5ths. Sit on
H:the destination note long enough to settle the tone before moving
H:on. NO RESTS — the long tones replace what would be silences in
H:a non-pipe instrument's interval drill.
% --- 2nds (step pairs) ---
G2 A2 | A2 B2 | B2 c2 | c2 d2 | d2 e2 | e2 f2 | f2 g2 | g2 a2 |
% --- 3rds ---
G2 B2 | A2 c2 | B2 d2 | c2 e2 | d2 f2 | e2 g2 | f2 a2 |
% --- 4ths ---
G2 c2 | A2 d2 | B2 e2 | c2 f2 | d2 g2 | e2 a2 |
% --- 5ths ---
G2 d2 | A2 e2 | B2 f2 | c2 g2 | d2 a2 |
